body:
@tahuang1991 is looking into how `CSCCLCTDigis` in a chamber correlate to the CLCT pre-trigger digi(s).  For detailed analyses we need to write out the pre-trigger digi as EDM products. Therefore Tao suggested to add the `CSCCLCTPreTriggerDigi` as a dataformat. These `CSCCLCTPreTriggerDigi`'s will not be used in the CSC local trigger nor in the CSC DAQ.  However, they are essential to understand the trigger and DAQ rates in Run-3 and Phase-2 when GEMs come online.

For now, the `CSCCLCTPreTriggerDigi` format is the same as for `CSCCLCTDigi`. In the future we may want to extend the dataformat with a list of half-strips that participated in the pre-trigger. For this reason we did not want to re-use the `CSCCLCTDigi` format.

I also added a template function in `CSCTriggerPrimitivesBuilder` which removes a lot of code-duplication.

@tahuang1991 @ptcox FYI
